<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10038h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10038h">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10038h"> 38(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> military ground sheet / to ensure correctness / of aim</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Labourer Shot / Strange Midnight Affray in Waterford / Volley in Ruins / Assailants Lie in Wait Near Victim&apos;s Home</b> <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Waterford City was alarmed by an outbreak of firing late last night, when it appears, shots were fired, wounding a young labourer named William Furlong, who resides at Costelloe&apos;s lane, as he was entering his home at 11.30 p.m.<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> According to his own story, Furlong was armed with a revolver and immediately returned the fire of his assailants, whose number he estimates as between nine and twelve.<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Victim Collapses Furlong collapsed opposite his own door on a <mark>military ground sheet</mark> which, according to his theory, was placed there previously by the attackers <mark>to ensure correctness of aim</mark>. <small> <a name="FJ11apr24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FJ11apr24"><cite title="source">Freeman's Journal</cite></a> (11 April 1924) 5/5</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01016h" href="c01all.htm#c01016h">VI.C.01:016(h)</a></mm></dd> </dd></dl>
